page.title: 17Ecology.
page.content: As our block is in the countryside there are very many wild birds. Most people have large kitchen gardens and lawns and these attract birds the most common being sparrows, tits, robins and wrens. Also some larger birds such as the magpie,jackdaws and crows come to our gardens. Two of our most common and poupular song birds are the blackbird and the thrush which are often seen feeding on slugs worms and snails. We have many summer visitors such as the house martain, swifts and swallow. The cuckoos also visits,however there seemed to be fewer this year and they were later than usual. The most common birds of prey seen on high ground in the area are buzzards tawny and barn owls and a few eagles in our block.
